notes.text:
This update for php8 fixes the following issues:

- CVE-2024-5458: Fixed an issue that allows to bypass filters in filter_var FILTER_VALIDATE_URL. (bsc#1226073)

notes.text: In PHP versions 8.1.* before 8.1.29, 8.2.* before 8.2.20, 8.3.* before 8.3.8, due to a code logic error, filtering functions such as filter_var when validating URLs (FILTER_VALIDATE_URL) for certain types of URLs the function will result in invalid user information (username + password part of URLs) being treated as valid user information. This may lead to the downstream code accepting invalid URLs as valid and parsing them incorrectly.
